# Astro

## Page layouts (`src/layouts/`)

- **`Layout.astro`**: `<html>`, meta/OG/Twitter, optional JSON-LD `schema`, Typekit, global SCSS, `LayoutHeader`, `<main class="site-main">`, `LayoutFooter`, `LayoutOffcanvas`, Analytics.
- **`ContentLayout.astro`**: Wraps `Layout` with `<article class="site-content">`.
- **Pages**: Thin composition — `getCollection()` / `getStaticPaths()` for dynamic routes. SEO via `title`, `description`, `schema` + `src/lib/*`.

**Prerender**: `export const prerender = true` per page when static HTML is wanted. Default is server (`astro.config.mjs`).

## UI components (`src/components/`)

Import page sections from `@components` (`src/components/index.ts`, Vite alias in `astro.config.mjs`).

### Blocks (`blocks/block-*.astro`)

Markup-only pieces with **no** `l-section` / `l-container`. BEM block name matches the file (e.g. `detail-list`, `button`, `project-card`).

Examples: `BlockButton`, `BlockButtonGroup`, `BlockDetailList`, `BlockProjectCard`, `BlockOffcanvasTrigger`.

### Layouts (`layouts/layout-*.astro`)

Section shells: own `l-section` / `l-container` (and related layout) as needed. Compose blocks and/or slots.

Examples: `LayoutHero`, `LayoutList2col`, `LayoutProjectGrid`, `LayoutAccordion`, `LayoutHeader`, `LayoutFooter`, `LayoutOffcanvas`.

**When to add a block:** only when markup is reused inside another layout’s slot (e.g. `BlockDetailList` inside `LayoutList2col`). If a layout is the sole consumer, keep all markup in that layout file — no paired `block-*`.

### Site chrome

`LayoutHeader`, `LayoutFooter`, and `LayoutOffcanvas` are wired in `Layout.astro` only — do not duplicate on pages. Mobile menu trigger: `BlockOffcanvasTrigger` (used inside `LayoutHeader`).

### Props & composition

- `interface Props { ... }`; destructure with defaults.
- `className` for modifiers; `class:list={[...]}` for conditionals.
- **`BlockButtonGroup` / `LayoutHero` / layouts with CTAs:** `primaryAction` and `secondaryAction` props (`Action` from `src/lib/actions.ts`). Omit prop → sitewide default; pass `null` → hide that action.

## BEM (markup)

| Prefix | Use |
|--------|-----|
| `site-*` | Header, footer, offcanvas |
| `l-*` | `l-section`, `l-container` |
| `u-*` | Utilities (`u-visually-hidden`) |
| block name | Matches component (`project-card`, `accordion`, `detail-list`) |

Modifiers: `block--modifier`, `block__element--modifier`.

## Content in `.astro`

- **Collections**: `getCollection("work" | "services" | "service-locations")` — schemas in `src/content/config.ts`.
- **Static JSON**: `import … from "../content/menu.json"` — `menu`, `reading`, `experience`, `social`.
- **MDX**: `await item.render()` + `<Content />` on work pages; service routes use layout components + frontmatter.

## Client `<script>` (in `.astro`)

- **Plain JS** — no `!`, no `as HTMLButtonElement`, no param types unless explicitly requested.
- **Co-locate** with the component that owns the behaviour (`layout-offcanvas.astro` has the menu script; `block-offcanvas-trigger.astro` stays script-free).
- **Select only `js-*` classes** — never `.site-offcanvas__panel`, `.offcanvas-menu__link`, etc.
- Pair each hook with BEM on the same node; don’t style `js-*` in SCSS.

### Reference: offcanvas

- Body state (for CSS): `offcanvas-active`, `offcanvas-closing` — toggled, not queried.
- Hooks: `js-site-offcanvas`, `js-site-offcanvas-panel`, `js-site-offcanvas-backdrop`, `js-site-offcanvas-trigger`, `js-site-offcanvas-close`, `js-offcanvas-menu-link`.
- ARIA: `aria-expanded` on trigger; `aria-hidden` + `inert` on root; `id="site-offcanvas"` for `aria-controls` only; `role="dialog"` on panel.
- Close: remove open class → add closing → `transitionend` on panel `transform` + timeout fallback (`1000ms + 100ms` ↔ `$transition-cubic-01`).
- Dismiss: close btn, backdrop, delegated menu links, `Escape`. Lock `body` overflow while open. Honor `prefers-reduced-motion`.

### Events

- Native events first (`click`, `keydown`, `transitionend`).
- Delegate from a stable parent when many children share behaviour.
